<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14509] AsyncOneResponse uses the incorrect timeout</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14509</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;AsyncOneResponse&lt;/tt&gt; has a bug where it uses the initial timeout value instead of the adjustedTimeout. Combined with passing in the wrong &lt;tt&gt;TimeUnit&lt;/tt&gt;, it leads to a shorter timeout than expected. This can have unintended consequences for example, in &lt;tt&gt;StorageService::sendReplicationNotification&lt;/tt&gt; instead of waiting 10 seconds (&lt;tt&gt;request_timeout_in_ms&lt;/tt&gt;), we wait for &lt;tt&gt;10000&lt;/tt&gt; Nano Seconds.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
